lkp_prm_type.PRM_TYPE_NOTES: BPI-12 is a medical survey with twelve questions used to measure pain, developed by the Pain Research Group of the WHO Collaborating Centre for Symptom Evaluation in Cancer Care.
BPI-4 is a medical survey with four questions used to measure pain, developed by the Pain Research Group of the WHO Collaborating Centre for Symptom Evaluation in Cancer Care.
EVS is a 2-question item asked of every patient during an outpatient visit.

PHQ-2 is a shorter version of the PHQ-9 with two screening questions to assess the presence of a depressed mood and a loss of interest or pleasure in routine activities; a positive response to either question indicates further testing is required.

PHQ-8 is an eight-question questionnaire established as a valid diagnostic and severity measure for depressive disorders in large clinical studies. The PHQ-8 is a useful depression measure for population-based studies.

lkp_prm_type.PRM_SUBTYPE_DESCRIPTION: Patient Health Questionnaire Modified for Teens - 2 (PHQ-T2 Modified)
lkp_prm_type.PRM_TYPE_NOTES: PHQ-T2 is a two-question well-accepted, standardized, validated questionnaire, used by many providers and health plans across the country. It can be used with patients between the ages of 11 and 20. It takes less than five minutes for them to complete.

lkp_prm_type.PRM_SUBTYPE_DESCRIPTION: Patient Health Questionnaire Modified for Teens - 8 (PHQ-T8 Modified)
lkp_prm_type.PRM_TYPE_NOTES: PHQ-T8 is an eight-question well-accepted, standardized, validated questionnaire, used by many providers and health plans across the country. It can be used with patients between the ages of 11 and 20. It takes less than five minutes for them to complete.

lkp_prm_type.PRM_SUBTYPE_DESCRIPTION: Patient Health Questionnaire Modified for Teens - 9 (PHQ-T9 Modified)
lkp_prm_type.PRM_TYPE_NOTES: PHQ-T9 is a nine-question well-accepted, standardized, validated questionnaire, used by many providers and health plans across the country. It can be used with patients between the ages of 11 and 20. It takes less than five minutes for them to complete.

lkp_prm_type.PRM_SUBTYPE_DESCRIPTION: Medicare Total Health Assessment - MTHA Questions
lkp_prm_type.PRM_TYPE_NOTES: MTHA is a questionnaire with 36 questions about a patient's health and day-to-day activities. This is used by the health care team to develop a plan to help a patient maintain or improve their health and well-being.

lkp_prm_type.PRM_SUBTYPE_DESCRIPTION: Medicare Total Health Assessment - EVS Questions
lkp_prm_type.PRM_TYPE_NOTES: The MTHA contains two EVS questions asked of every patient during an outpatient visit.

lkp_prm_type.PRM_SUBTYPE_DESCRIPTION: Medicare Total Health Assessment - GAD-2 Questions
lkp_prm_type.PRM_TYPE_NOTES: The MTHA contains the GAD-2 questions to assess generalized anxiety disorder, normally used in outpatient and primary care settings for referral to psychiatrist pending outcome.

lkp_prm_type.PRM_SUBTYPE_DESCRIPTION: Medicare Total Health Assessment - PHQ-2 Questions
lkp_prm_type.PRM_TYPE_NOTES: The MTHA contains the PHQ-2 screening questions to assess the presence of a depressed mood and a loss of interest or pleasure in routine activities; a positive response to either question indicates further testing is required.
AUDIT-10 is a simple ten-question test developed by the World Health Organization to determine if a person's alcohol consumption may be harmful.
AUDIT-2 is a simple two-question test developed by the World Health Organization to determine if a person's alcohol consumption may be harmful.
AUDIT-C is a simple three-question test developed by the World Health Organization to determine if a person's alcohol consumption may be harmful.
GAD-2 is a two-question sensitive self-administrated test to assess generalized anxiety disorder, normally used in outpatient and primary care settings for referral to psychiatrist pending outcome.
GAD-7 is a seven-question sensitive self-administrated test to assess generalized anxiety disorder, normally used in outpatient and primary care settings for referral to psychiatrist pending outcome.

The PEG is an ultra-brief measure of pain derived from the Brief Pain Inventory measure. PEG stands for Pain intensity, Enjoyment of life, General Activity. The BPI sleep related question is often also included.
The PROMIS is a series of self-report measures for adults and covers different functions, symptoms, behaviors and feelings in the domains of physical, mental and social health.
The YCLS is a 10-question, KP developed measure used to evaluate social needs of members. There are additional item-bank questions that can be added to the core measure.
The SF-36 is a 36-item, patient-reported survey of patient health and quality-of-life.
The SF-12 is a shorter, 12-item version of the SF Health Survey that is used to primarily to measure physical and mental health.

lkp_prm_type.PRM_SUBTYPE_DESCRIPTION: Medicare Total Health Assessment - YCLS Questions
lkp_prm_type.PRM_TYPE_NOTES: The MTHA contains YCLS questions asked during an outpatient visit.
